text.section:
"Unit price" means the retail price of an item expressed in dollars and cents per unit. In addition to any units commonly in use in the United States, the following units may be used if appropriate:
Per pound for an item the net quantity of which is expressed in pounds, ounces, or both;
Per kilogram (1000 grams) for an item the net quantity of which is expressed in kilograms, grams, or both;
Per meter (100 centimeters) for an item the net quantity of which is expressed in meters, centimeters, millimeters, or a combination of them;
Per quart for an item the net quantity of which is expressed in quarts, pints, fluid ounces, or a combination of them;
Per liter for an item the net quantity of which is expressed in liters and milliliters, or a combination of them;
Per 100 feet for an item the net quantity of which is expressed in yards, feet, inches, or a combination of them;
Per 100 square feet for an item the net quantity of which is expressed in square yards, square feet, square inches, or a combination of them; or
Per 100 units for an item the net quantity of which is expressed in terms of a numerical count.
